
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `cc` yek dastoor baraye compile kardan (tabdil kardan code be barnameye ejraee) code-haye zaban C ast.  Be ebarate digar, code-haye C ra migirad va anha ra be barnameye ghabele ejra tabdil mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `cc file.c` --> 🚀 Tabdil file.c be yek barnameye ghabele ejra ba name "a.out".
    🔹 `cc file.c -o barname` --> 🎯 Tabdil file.c be yek barnameye ghabele ejra ba name "barname".
    🔹 `cc file.c -Wall` --> 🚧 Namayesh hameye etela'ati ke momken ast dar code moshkel ijad konad.
    🔹 `cc file.c -lm` --> ➕ Ezafe kardane ketabkhanehaye riazi (math library) baraye estefade az function haye riazi mesle sin, cos, va...

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ cc hello.c

    🔹 Tabdil file hello.c be barname "a.out" (age khata nabashe)

    $ cc hello.c -o hello

    🔹 Tabdil file hello.c be barname "hello".

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ cc program.c -o program

    🔹 In dastoor code-haye mojood dar file `program.c` ra compile mikonad va yek barnameye ghabele ejra ba name `program` misazad.  Shoma mitavanid barname ra ba dastoor `./program` ejra konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `cc` command is used to compile (convert code to an executable program) C language code.  In other words, it takes C source code and transforms it into an executable.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `cc file.c` --> 🚀 Compile file.c into an executable program named "a.out".
    🔹 `cc file.c -o program` --> 🎯 Compile file.c into an executable program named "program".
    🔹 `cc file.c -Wall` --> 🚧 Display all warnings, which might indicate potential problems in the code.
    🔹 `cc file.c -lm` --> ➕ Link the math library to use mathematical functions like sin, cos, etc.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ cc hello.c

    🔹 Compiles the file hello.c into a program named "a.out" (if there are no errors).

    $ cc hello.c -o hello

    🔹 Compiles the file hello.c into a program named "hello".

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ cc program.c -o program

    🔹 This command compiles the C code in the file `program.c` and creates an executable program named `program`. You can then run the program using `./program`.
